26    /**
27    * This class represents a curve build from a set of points in 2D.
28    *
29    * It provides different interpolation and extrapolation methods applied to a transformation of the input point,
30    * examples are
31    * <ul>
32    * <li>linear interpolation of the input points</li>
33    * <li>linear interpolation of the log of the input points</li>
34    * <li>linear interpolation of the log of the input points divided by their respective time</li>
35    * <li>cubic spline interpolation of the input points (or a function of the input points) (the curve will be C<sup>1</sup>).</li>
36    * <li>Akima interpolation of the input points (or a function of the input points).</li>
37    * <li>etc.</li>
38    * </ul>
39    *

41    *
42    * For the interpolation methods provided see {@link net.finmath.marketdata.model.curves.CurveInterpolation.InterpolationMethod}.

44    * For the possible interpolation entities see {@link net.finmath.marketdata.model.curves.CurveInterpolation.InterpolationEntity}.
45    *
